projects.description:
- Worked with a team of 5 other young professionals from TNO, from across the organization to create a social business case for addressing energy poverty;
- Used a design-thinking approach towards addressing the challenge; team interviewed 8 municipalities and over 20 subject-matter experts in TNO to identify the core problem;
- Solution developed involved the use of privacy-enhancing technologies for the combination of individual data from various sources including the Municipality, CBS and UWV to securely identify the individuals in need of urgent assistance;
- Conducted the business case modeling and impact assessment for the project;
- Solution adopted by TNO as a new proposition, and a pilot is being designed in collaboration with the Municipality of Rotterdam;
- Awarded the Future Maker Award by the Partnership Verkieizing (an initiative of The Punchy Pack, the Ministry of External Affairs (The Netherlands), and the Rotterdam School of Management).

profile_positions.description:
Department: Integrated Vehicle Safety

The department Integrated Vehicle Safety works with the government and various international industrial partners on assessing and developing smart and safety-oriented vehicle technlogies. My work primarily focuses on autonomous driving and yard automation topics.

 As a Project Manager within the team, I am responsible for the scope, budget, quality, customer relations and team satisfaction for my running projects as well as leading the acquisition of new projects:
- Responsible for a portfolio of 3 research proects, with a total project size of €4,1 Million;
- Working with teams of between 3 and 15 researchers, spanning 3 departments and units of TNO;
- Collaborating with between 1 and 7 external partners;
- Also responsible for 3 business-to-business projects in the acquisition stage, with large automotive companies across Europe with a total budget of €600.000.
